<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> don’t even think of it • don’t give it a thought</xh5><p> <i>don’t even think of it—</i>don’t even let such an idea occur to you; don’t even consider such a possibility: With high summer temperatures, you’ll need to be drinking water constantly. Drugs: <u>Don’t even think of it</u>.</p><p><i>don’t give it a thought</i>—(also: don’t give it a second thought) 1. let that not worry you: I was eating regular food within five days after surgery. So, <u>don’t give it a thought</u>! 2. is used to indicate that thanks are unnecessary: “Thank you very much for all your help!” “Please <u>don’t give it a thought</u>!” 3. is used as a polite way of accepting apology: “I’m sorry that I treated you mean today.” “Oh, <u>don’t give it a thought</u>.”</p> </entry>
